<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1230,2011]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1230,1255]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished by the uniformly fuscous to black body (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1182,1230,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1502,1525]" captionTargetBox="[260,1321,434,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-238@3.[228,1360,419,1505]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Aristotelesia fuscata (holotype). 1, dorsal aspect; 2, lateral aspect; 3, head and pronotum, dorsal aspect; 4, head, lateral aspect; 5, head, frontal aspect." pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
) and dark brown legs, with only the antennae pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[570,681,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1502,1525]" captionTargetBox="[260,1321,434,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-238@3.[228,1360,419,1505]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Aristotelesia fuscata (holotype). 1, dorsal aspect; 2, lateral aspect; 3, head and pronotum, dorsal aspect; 4, head, lateral aspect; 5, head, frontal aspect." pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henry &amp; Carpintero" authorityYear="2012" box="[807,935,1267,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Aristotelesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medialis">
<emphasis box="[807,935,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">A. medialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is bluish black, with orange femora and an orange head with a dark median line, and 
<taxonomicName box="[620,737,1302,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Aristotelesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carioca">
<emphasis box="[620,737,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">A. carioca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is uniformly black with the antennae and legs pale yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
